Methods in ej.mwt with parameters of type Renderer
 int Desktop.computeScore(Renderer renderer)
           Computes the score of the given renderer by comparing the Desktop.getStyle() of the desktop with the getManagedStyle() of the specified renderer.
The score is bigger when the renderer matches the style and lower when it does not match.
The score is computed using the RenderingContext.computeScore(int, int) algorithm.
 int Widget.computeScore(Renderer renderer)
           Computes the score of the given renderer by comparing the Widget.getStyle() of the widget with the getManagedStyle() of the specified renderer.
 int Renderable.computeScore(Renderer renderer)
           Computes the score of the given renderer, normally by comparing the Renderable.getStyle() of the renderable with the getManagedStyle() of the specified renderer.
The score is bigger when the renderer matches the style and lower when it does not match.
 int Panel.computeScore(Renderer renderer)
           Computes the score of the given renderer by comparing the Panel.getStyle() of the panel with the getManagedStyle() of the specified renderer.
The score is bigger when the renderer matches the style and lower when it does not match.
The score is computed using the RenderingContext.computeScore(int, int) algorithm.
